-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. DEFINITIONS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"Software" refers to the SecureSeaHorse SIEM platform, including but not
limited to the C++ source code (Client/Server and all headers in src/server/
and src/client/), build scripts, CMake configuration, installer scripts for
Linux and Windows, certificate generation helpers, configuration templates
(server.conf, client.conf, rules.conf), built-in threat intelligence feeds,
dashboard HTML/JavaScript, and all documentation (README, USER_MANUAL,
changelogs).

"Authorized User" means an individual or entity granted express written
permission by Secured Cyber Solutions Limited to access and use the Software.

"Security Protocols" refers to the mutual TLS (mTLS) implementation, HMAC-SHA256
packet integrity checks, RFC 5705 keying material exporter, certificate
revocation list (CRL) support, OCSP stapling, SHA-256 certificate pinning,
and the v2 binary wire protocol inherent to the Software's operation.

"Detection Engines" refers to the proprietary analysis subsystems including
the Traffic Classifier (6 attack categories with MITRE ATT&CK mapping),
Threat Intelligence engine (7 IoC types with feed auto-reload), Regex
Analysis Engine, Alert Engine, File Integrity Monitor, Process Monitor,
Connection Inventory, Session & Authentication Tracker, Software Inventory,
Network Deep Inspector (DNS/protocol/entropy analyzers), and the
Correlation Engine with its kill-chain rule library.

"Response Subsystems" refers to the Incident Response Engine with its
playbook library, IP blocklist, device quarantine, audit trail, the
Agent Fleet Manager, and the REST API server with embedded web dashboard.

"Derivative Work" means any modification, adaptation, translation, or work
based upon the Software, including but not limited to ports to other
programming languages, alternative protocol implementations that preserve
the Software's detection logic, or forks incorporating substantial portions
of the Detection Engines or Response Subsystems.

"Third-Party Components" refers to open-source libraries the Software
depends on at build or run time, including OpenSSL, libpq (PostgreSQL
client library), and the Nullsoft Scriptable Install System (NSIS). Each
Third-Party Component is governed by its own license, and nothing in this
Agreement alters those terms.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. GRANT OF LICENSE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Subject to the terms of this Agreement, Secured Cyber Solutions Limited
grants the Authorized User a non-exclusive, non-transferable, non-sublicensable,
and revocable license to:

    A. Install and execute the Software on systems owned or controlled by
       the Authorized User, for internal security monitoring, telemetry
       collection, threat detection, incident response, and compliance
       reporting purposes.

    B. Deploy the Client agent to endpoints within the Authorized User's
       organization in reasonable quantities commensurate with the
       monitoring scope agreed in writing.

    C. Modify local configuration files (server.conf, client.conf,
       rules.conf) and add custom threat intelligence feed files (CSV)
       to tailor the Software to the Authorized User's environment.

    D. Generate and manage the Authorized User's own TLS certificates,
       CA material, and API tokens for use with the Software.

This license does not constitute a sale of the Software or any copies
thereof. All right, title, and interest in and to the Software remain
the exclusive property of Secured Cyber Solutions Limited.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. RESTRICTIONS & SECURITY INTEGRITY
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To maintain the security posture and proprietary nature of the
SecureSeaHorse ecosystem, the following actions are strictly prohibited:

    A. REVERSE ENGINEERING: You may not decompile, disassemble, or attempt
       to derive the source code or underlying algorithms of compiled
       binaries distributed without source, particularly the Security
       Protocols, the Detection Engines, the Correlation Engine's rule
       matching logic, the adaptive baseline (EWMA) calculations, or the
       Network Deep Inspector's entropy and DGA detection heuristics.

    B. CIRCUMVENTION: Any attempt to bypass, modify, or tamper with the
       mTLS authentication, HMAC-SHA256 packet integrity verification,
       certificate pinning, bearer token authentication on the REST API,
       HTML escaping in the web dashboard, or the input-validation caps
       added in v3.1.1 (HTTP parser limits, regex input caps, feed loader
       caps, SQL parameter clamping) is a material breach of this license.

    C. REDISTRIBUTION: You may not sub-license, rent, lease, lend, sell,
       resell, assign, or otherwise transfer the Software, in whole or in
       part, to any third party without prior express written consent from
       Secured Cyber Solutions Limited.

    D. DERIVATIVE WORKS: You may not create, distribute, or publish
       Derivative Works based on the Software. This includes but is not
       limited to ports, rewrites, plugins, or standalone tools that
       incorporate or imitate the Detection Engines, Response Subsystems,
       Correlation Engine rules, or wire protocol.

    E. COMPETING PRODUCTS: You may not use the Software, any part of its
       source code, or any insights gained from studying its source to
       develop, market, or sell a product that competes with SecureSeaHorse
       in the SIEM, EDR, or security monitoring markets.

    F. REMOVAL OF NOTICES: You may not remove, alter, or obscure any
       copyright, trademark, author attribution, or license notices
       contained in the Software.

    G. MALICIOUS USE: You may not use the Software to conduct unauthorized
       surveillance, to monitor systems you do not have legal authority to
       monitor, or in any manner that violates applicable laws or the
       privacy rights of others.

    H. BENCHMARKING & PUBLIC DISCLOSURE: You may not publish benchmarks,
       performance comparisons, vulnerability disclosures (other than
       private reports to Secured Cyber Solutions Limited under a
       responsible disclosure process), or security assessments of the
       Software without prior written consent.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. CONFIDENTIALITY
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Software contains trade secrets and proprietary information of
Secured Cyber Solutions Limited, including but not limited to:

    - The internal directory structures and module organization
    - The Detection Engines' heuristics, thresholds, and baseline algorithms
    - The Correlation Engine's kill-chain rule library and scoring formulas
    - The Incident Response Engine's playbook definitions and cooldown logic
    - Configuration templates and their semantics
    - The v2 wire protocol message format and HMAC derivation method
    - Cryptographic methodologies layered above the public-domain OpenSSL
      primitives the Software calls into

The Authorized User shall maintain the Software in strict confidence and
shall not disclose any of the above to any unauthorized third party. This
confidentiality obligation survives termination of this Agreement.

Nothing in this section restricts disclosure of information that is:
(a) publicly known through no fault of the Authorized User, (b) already in
the Authorized User's possession prior to disclosure, or (c) required to
be disclosed by law or court order (provided the Authorized User gives
prompt written notice to Secured Cyber Solutions Limited where legally
permitted).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. DATA PRIVACY & TELEMETRY
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Authorized User acknowledges that SecureSeaHorse is designed to
collect, process, and store security-relevant data including:

    - System performance metrics (CPU, RAM, disk, network)
    - System logs (Syslog, Windows Event Log)
    - File integrity hashes and modification events
    - Running processes with command lines and owners
    - Active TCP/UDP network connections
    - Interactive user sessions and authentication events (successful
      logins, failed logins, source IP addresses, sudo/runas events)
    - Installed software inventory with versions
    - Correlated multi-stage attack incidents spanning multiple devices

It is the Authorized User's sole responsibility to ensure that the
deployment of this Software complies with all applicable local, national,
and international data protection laws (e.g., GDPR, UK GDPR, CCPA, HIPAA,
PIPEDA), to obtain any required employee or data-subject consents, to
publish any required privacy notices, and to implement appropriate data
retention and deletion policies within PostgreSQL and the Software's
log files.

Secured Cyber Solutions Limited is not liable for the sensitive nature of
the data collected, transmitted, stored, or displayed via the Software, or
for any regulatory consequences of the Authorized User's deployment choices.

