11. TERMINATION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This license is effective from the date the Authorized User first installs
or uses the Software and continues until terminated.

The Authorized User's rights under this license will terminate automatically
and without notice if the Authorized User fails to comply with any term of
this Agreement. Secured Cyber Solutions Limited may also terminate this
license at any time with thirty (30) days' written notice.

Upon termination:

    A. The Authorized User shall immediately cease all use of the Software.
    B. The Authorized User shall destroy all copies of the Software, full
       or partial, in their possession or control, including binaries,
       source code, configuration files, and documentation.
    C. The Authorized User shall revoke all TLS certificates issued under
       the Software's CA and purge all telemetry and event data from the
       PostgreSQL database, unless retention is required by law.
    D. Sections 3 (Restrictions), 4 (Confidentiality), 7 (Intellectual
       Property), 8 (No Warranty), 9 (Limitation of Liability), 10
       (Export Control), and 13 (Governing Law) shall survive termination.

